    'cerocup_rules': 'Promotion rules description',
    'cerocup_rules_con':
        'The Champions League main game is divided into group stage, 1/8 finals, 1/4 finals, semi-finals and finals. The group stage is divided into 8 groups, with 4 teams in each group. Each team will play two home and away matches with the other three opponents in the same group. The top two in the group advance to the Champions League 1/8 finals, and the third place in the group will advance to the Champions League 1/8 finals. Participate in the UEFA Europa League knockout playoffs. In the 1/8 finals, quarter finals and semi-finals, each team will play two home and away games with its opponents. The promotion rules are the same as the qualifying stage and play-offs; the 1/8 finals are from teams in the same group and association. They will not meet, but starting from the quarter-finals this rule is no longer valid. ',
